---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="What happens if you delete Windows System32?" description="Learn why deleting System32 breaks Windows and why it's not a safe experiment.">
  <article class="post-container">
    <header class="post-header">
      <a class="back-link" href="/blog/">← Back to Blog</a>
      <h1>What Happens if You Delete Windows System32?</h1>
      <p class="post-meta">August 20, 2025 | By Dog Expert Tech</p>
    </header>

    <img src="/gallery/assets/wallpapers/Nebula-2.png" alt="System32 Blog" class="post-image" loading="lazy" />

    <div class="post-body">
      <p class="warning">⚠️ WARNING: DO NOT DO THIS! Deleting the Windows System32 folder will render your system unusable and may cause permanent data loss.</p>

      <p>System32 contains core Windows files, drivers, and services. If you remove this folder, your system will not boot and may crash immediately. Usually, the only recovery option is a clean reinstall of Windows.</p>

      <p>This post and the video below are for <strong>educational purposes only</strong>. Never try this on a real machine.</p>

      <p>If you want to experiment safely, do it in a Virtual Machine.</p>

      <div class="video-container">
        <iframe loading="lazy" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/XYor-ML__iE" title="YouTube video player" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe>
      </div>

      <img src="/blog/b1089010/assets/rdcmd.png" alt="Remote command screenshot" class="post-image" loading="lazy" />

      <h2>Why This Breaks Windows</h2>
      <p>The System32 folder includes drivers, core libraries, and utilities that Windows relies on every second. Removing it corrupts the operating system and interrupts startup.</p>
    </div>

    <footer class="post-footer">
      <div id="google_translate_element"></div>
      <p>&copy; 2026 Dog Expert Tech</p>
    </footer>
  </article>

  <script type="text/javascript">
    function googleTranslateElementInit() {
      new google.translate.TranslateElement({
        pageLanguage: 'en',
        includedLanguages: 'en,et,ru',
        layout: google.translate.TranslateElement.InlineLayout.SIMPLE
      }, 'google_translate_element');
    }
  </script>
  <script src="//translate.google.com/translate_a/element.js?cb=googleTranslateElementInit" async defer></script>
</Layout>

